result.execSummary:
The defendant Dangelo D Gaynor-Peterson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Robbery with Threat of Force, a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.32(1)(b).
  • Vehicle Operator Flee/Elude Officer, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.04(3).
  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Court finds defendant IS NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration program and the WI Substance Abuse program.

- Obtain/maintain employment, education or combination of both.
- No contact with: DC, Shieta G. and the Gas station at 7609 W. Capitol Dr. Milwaukee WI. 
- Provide a DNA sample.
- Follow all rules of supervision and follow through with any other treatment deemed necessary by the department.

-Court ordered the defendant pay all of the following by the end of supervision. 
DNA surcharge. 
Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment:

Court WAIVES all court costs, fees, and surcharges (EXCEPT DNA SURCHARGE) due to the length of imprisionment and ability to pay; 
-  Court ordered that DNA surcharge be paid through collection by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision. DOC shall collect those sums.  
Any amount remaining due by 08/19/2031, any remaining balance is subject to civil judgment and/or tax intercept or other means.

Defendant Dangelo D Gaynor-Peterson in court with Attorney Thomas Evangelos Harris.  Defendant Dangelo D Gaynor-Peterson in custody.  Ann R. Lopez, appearing for Ben Wesson, appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Count 1 amended on the Amended Information.
Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the State, Court orders penalty enhancer DISMISSED as to amended count 1 and counts 3 and 4.

As to Counts 1, 3 and 4:
Defendant advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties; waives constitutional rights, enters a plea of  GUILTY  to the amended charges and is examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the Complaint as a factual basis for judgment.  Court finds defendant guilty as charged in the Information/Complaint and orders a judgment of conviction be entered.

As to Count  2 and Count  5:
Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the State, Court orders Counts 2 and 5  DISMISSED but read-in as to sentencing.

COURT ADVISES the defendant he cannot possess firearms; further, defendant is advised he cannot vote until his civil rights are restored.  Defendant was further advised that if not a United States citizen deportation is possible. 

State's request for PSI; defense counsel objects.
PSI ordered without recommendation.  Court orders case adjourned for sentencing in Branch 28.  Jury trial is vacated.

All parties are notified that effective August 1, 2016 this case will be assigned to Judge Christopher Dee, Branch 37,  in Room 313 of the Safety Bldg.
